track_notes: This is an easy family summit; not very nice, you walk on a forest road, then at the end you must look for the trig point in between vegetation!

You must park near the water tank (road is not allowed), that makes 7km to the summit (14km a day).
It is nearly the same path, but in winter time when the forest road is icy (very slick, a bit dangerous), it is better to choose an easy way until you reach the Bergerie; then follow the path along electrical wire where dogs are barking to you. Not far from summit go to the right to find the summit in vegetation, plenty room for antenna.
